data.meta_description: Blanche of Navarre (1226 – 12 August 1283), also known as Blanche of Champagne, was the daughter of Theobald the Troubador, King of Navarre and Count of Champagne,and his second wife Agnes of Beaujeu. She was a member of the House of Champagne.  Blanche was firstly betrothed to Otto III, Count of Burgundy; the marriage...
